WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.780
Okay. My disclosures. So is Hodgkin a heterogeneous disease? So the obvious answer is yes, everything

00:00:11.780 --> 00:00:18.080
is heterogeneous. If you look into the WHO classification currently, Hodgkin lymphoma

00:00:18.080 --> 00:00:23.500
is mainly divided by the appearance of the tumor microenvironment. That's just the biology

00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:30.500
of the disease, that there is a very heterogeneous mix of cells with the malignant cells in the

00:00:30.500 --> 00:00:38.240
minority. And these ecosystems are still very poorly understood, both the malignant cell

00:00:38.240 --> 00:00:44.160
genomics and then corresponding tumor microenvironment inflammatory reactions. So really an integrative

00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:49.820
approach is needed to come up with something better that is clinically relevant. So if

00:00:49.820 --> 00:00:53.480
you look into these four subtypes, nodular sclerosis, neuroendocrine, neuromuscular disease,

00:00:53.480 --> 00:00:58.760
mixed cilillarity, lymphocyte depleted, lymphocyte rich, so all of these don't really have a

00:00:58.760 --> 00:01:03.360
bearing on clinical decision making. And then the nodular lymphocyte predominant that you

00:01:03.360 --> 00:01:10.960
see on the far right here, so that's likely to lose the age and the Hodgkin might be dropped

00:01:10.960 --> 00:01:17.720
in future classifications. So we need to come up with something biologically informed and

00:01:17.720 --> 00:01:23.460
just also to polarize a little bit here. And I know that my co-speakers will expand on that,

00:01:23.460 --> 00:01:29.680
but just to polarize, there's regional differences in how people think about how to treat and

00:01:29.680 --> 00:01:38.940
there's two breakthrough studies that are, I'm sure, cited often in the next talks as

00:01:38.940 --> 00:01:46.980
well. New England Journal 2024, the volume of AVD being superior to BV AVD and then the

00:01:46.980 --> 00:01:53.440
more European interpretation, they are holding on to brentuximab and treatment intensification.

00:01:53.440 --> 00:01:58.960
So there's different thoughts, and the thoughts are mostly biologically uninformed, I would say.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:08.160
And so we tackled the problem by starting from the ground up with an integrative genomic study design,

00:02:09.040 --> 00:02:14.880
basically doing everything we can at the moment with modern technologies, single cell, spatial

00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:22.640
transcriptomics, TME characterizations by imaging mass cytometry, have Hodgkin-Reed-Sternberg cells

00:02:22.640 --> 00:02:23.420
microdissected, and then we can do a lot of other things, and then we can do a lot of other things

00:02:23.420 --> 00:02:23.480
as well. We can do a lot of other things, and then we can do a lot of other things, and then we can do a lot of other things

00:02:23.480 --> 00:02:29.640
that flow-sorted, and then for the same samples put onto tissue microarrays so that we can read

00:02:29.640 --> 00:02:35.720
out on the tumor microenvironment, and then outcome correlates and modeling as well.

00:02:36.320 --> 00:02:42.200
So this is the essence of the study that is now published in Cancer Discovery just a couple of

00:02:42.200 --> 00:02:49.000
weeks ago, where we discovered, based on NMF clustering on the mutational profiles, we just

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:53.400
have four types that we labeled CST-CN91.

00:02:53.400 --> 00:03:00.340
3 STB and CN2P, so these are code names for actually the mutations that are found in these

00:03:00.340 --> 00:03:08.020
clusters, either copy number or simple mutations. And you can see on the right-hand side here that

00:03:08.020 --> 00:03:17.300
there's correlates to age and EBV, which there's hints in the literature, of course, that there is

00:03:17.980 --> 00:03:22.340
relevance to EBV positivity versus negative disease, and also

00:03:23.380 --> 00:03:29.100
individual mutations have been described before that are more enriched in pediatric or adolescent

00:03:29.100 --> 00:03:34.140
young adult lymphoma versus elderly Hodgkin lymphoma, so I don't want to linger too much

00:03:34.140 --> 00:03:42.860
on that. So this tool to distinguish now four Hodgkin lymphoma types is available as a tool

00:03:42.860 --> 00:03:50.420
publicly downloadable. We call it HLGEN, which has an unclassifiable group, and then the four

00:03:50.420 --> 00:03:53.360
types that I just referenced to you. And the good thing about this tool is that it's not just

00:03:53.360 --> 00:03:58.340
a single-use tool, it can be used to do a lot of other things. So the good news is this pretty much

00:03:58.340 --> 00:04:02.720
aligns with an earlier publication by Ash Elizadeh, who is in the conference, I don't see him here,

